                            <comment id="12666380" author="jimk" created="Fri, 23 Jan 2009 01:22:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;During &quot;safe mode&quot; the master should accept all connections from region servers and assign them some (but maybe not a&lt;br/&gt;
balanced) load of regions. Do you still have this issue with 0.19.0 or trunk?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12711408" author="stack" created="Wed, 20 May 2009 23:07:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think we need to remove the switch where we decide there is 1 or N servers.  Thats the way to guarantee we don&apos;t run into above issue.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12746329" author="stack" created="Fri, 21 Aug 2009 22:55:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fix as part of master rewrite in 0.21&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12867057" author="streamy" created="Thu, 13 May 2010 05:27:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;New load balancer as part of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-2485&quot; title=&quot;Persist Master in-memory state so on restart or failover, new instance can pick up where the old left off&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-2485&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-2485&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; should fix this.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12904923" author="stack" created="Wed, 1 Sep 2010 05:31:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;New LoadBalancer added by &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-2692&quot; title=&quot;Master rewrite and cleanup for 0.90&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-2692&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-2692&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; does away with this &apos;single-server-only&apos; notion.  The prob. described above is no longer possible&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15017815" author="lars_francke" created="Fri, 20 Nov 2015 13:01:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This issue was closed as part of a bulk closing operation on 2015-11-20. All issues that have been resolved and where all fixVersions have been released have been closed (following discussions on the mailing list).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
